    "overallReasoning": {
      "summary": "Three-tier architecture using VMSS for presentation and application tiers with SQL Managed Instance as the encrypted backend. Network isolation is enforced through dedicated subnets with NSGs. The presentation tier is autoscaled behind a Standard Load Balancer with zone-redundancy across three availability zones. SQL MI uses a delegated subnet with service-aided configuration, providing TDE encryption by default and a private-only data endpoint.",
      "tradeoffs": "This architecture uses IaaS (VMSS) over PaaS, giving full OS-level control at the cost of higher operational overhead. The L4 Load Balancer does not provide WAF or SSL offload — consider upgrading to Application Gateway if L7 features are needed. SQL MI General Purpose tier uses remote storage; upgrade to Business Critical for local SSD and read replicas."
    },
    "validation": "All resources deploy to eastus. Standard SKU public IP matches Standard LB. SQL MI subnet is delegated to Microsoft.Sql/managedInstances with required NSG and route table. Subnets are non-overlapping within 10.0.0.0/16. VMSS zones [1,2,3] align with zone-redundant public IP and LB.",
